olicy changes. Conceived of as a book for gender and society classes with a mix of exciting, accessible, pointed pieces, Gender in the Twenty-First Century is an ideal book for students and scholars alike.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aEquality before the lawzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aSex discrimination in employmentzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aSex role in the work environmentzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aSex rolezUnited Statesy21st century. 0aWork and familyzUnited Statesy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aDavis, Shannon N., eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520965188423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520965188.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles